reviews.review_text: another good one another good show,who is the woman talking on tuning track 11,sounds like she is having an orgasm!
3-1-87 Another nice '87 show and another fine remastered soundboard by Charlie. In the quieter moments you can hear the tape generations hiss if that bothers you.

Very enjoyable show. Sound mix gets better as set 1 develops. Vast improvement over the Chinese New Year shows, so far. Space is noteworthy for being a lot more jammy than spacey. Very well-played altogether.

Post drums The Fired On the Mountain really shreds. The post drums on this show is great. "Space" is mislabeled out of habit. It should be called "jam", because that's what it is. Drummers and all. The Other One is short, but it doesn't really seem that way because it's really an extension of the jam.

Black Peter is one of the best versions I've ever heard. The outro jam is reminiscent of the Dekalb '77 version.

I don't know if the Dead got much better than this in 1987. Plus the recording quality is great.
